CLIMATE CHANGE & EMERGING INFECTIONS (7)
========================================
Recent articles on Climate Change and Health
A number of articles on impact of climate change on human health have just
been published which may be of interest to ProMED users because most discuss
the potential effects on infectious diseases.
1. McMichael AJ, Ando M, Carcavallo R, at al. Human Population Health. In
Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change Working Group II Second Assessment
Report. Geneva: World Meterological Organisation/United Nations Environment
Programme, 1995. [Should be available from: IPCC Secretariat, WMO, Geneva,
E-mail: <narasimhan.sundararaman@itu.ch>]
2. Jackson EK. Climate change and global infectious disease threats. Medical
Journal of Australia 163, 1995: 570-575. [Available from me.]
3. Hales S, Woodward A, Guest C. Climate change in the South Pacific and
public health research. Australian Journal of Public Health 19, 1995: 543-545.
4. Health and Climate Change. Medicine and War 11, 1995. [Eight articles:
Editorial (Holdstock D); Basic Science of Climate Change (Maskell K); Health
Impacts of Climate Change (Kovats S, Haines A); Climate Change and Wood Food
Supply (Parry ML, Parry CJ); Climate Change and Health in the UK (Rowland
MGM); Challenges in Predicting Health Impacts (McMichael AJ); Climate Change
and Malaria (Martens WJM); Climate Change Convention and Human Health (Suter
K).]
